    {
      "id": "PopularPost306135",
      "post_content": "This card brings back fond memories of playing *The Sparkler* precon deck from Stronghold. Precons were just different then - there was so much power and strategy involved, rather than just showcasing a keyword or guild/set mechanic. This deck required so much skill to play, because it was all about timing, choices, stalling, and getting to 6 mana with no acceleration so you could buyback your spells and eventually win with either this or [Fanning the Flames](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fanning the Flames). 2 walls and [Mogg Fanatic](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mogg Fanatic) were the only creatures in that deck, so you were counting on being able to grab all of your opponents' creatures and swinging with them on an empty board. More often than not, you were playing from behind the entire time, until finally able to stabilize the board and in full-on desperation mode, a turn or two away from losing. It showcased the fact that Magic is a game of choices - do I use my singleton [Ransack](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ransack) to search for an answer... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Equinox523",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost306135\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_post\">This card brings back fond memories of playing <i>The Sparkler</i> precon deck from Stronghold.  Precons were just different then - there was so much power and strategy involved, rather than just showcasing a keyword or guild/set mechanic.  This deck required so much skill to play, because it was all about timing, choices, stalling, and getting to 6 mana with no acceleration so you could buyback your spells and eventually win with either this or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Fanning the Flames\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fanning the Flames\">Fanning the Flames</a>.  2 walls and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mogg Fanatic\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mogg Fanatic\">Mogg Fanatic</a> were the only creatures in that deck, so you were counting on being able to grab all of your opponents' creatures and swinging with them on an empty board.  More often than not, you were playing from behind the entire time, until finally able to stabilize the board and in full-on desperation mode, a turn or two away from losing.  It showcased the fact that Magic is a game of choices - do I use my singleton <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ransack\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ransack\">Ransack</a> to search for an answer... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 306135)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '306135'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy1136\">Equinox523</span>\r\n                                (3/28/2013 10:35:32 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>"
